# CODEOWNERS for Avidelta Repository
#
# This file defines code ownership aligned with the dot-rail branch protection ruleset.
# Code owners are automatically requested for review when someone opens a PR that
# modifies files in their defined paths.
#
# Learn more: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# =============================================================================
# AUTOMATION & INFRASTRUCTURE (Critical Paths - dot-rail ruleset)
# =============================================================================

# Python automation scripts - core business logic
# Includes daily_v2.py, update_security_dashboard.py, csp-reporter.js, and all modules
scripts/                    @dotlink-ops

# Python library modules - shared automation logic
python/                     @dotlink-ops

# GitHub Actions workflows - CI/CD and automation orchestration
# Any change to workflows affects production automation runs
.github/workflows/          @dotlink-ops

# Actions configuration
.github/actions/            @dotlink-ops

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY & CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================

# Security documentation - requires security review
docs/SECURITY*.md           @dotlink-ops
docs/PRE_COMMIT_GUIDE.md    @dotlink-ops
docs/BRANCH_PROTECTION.md   @dotlink-ops
SECURITY_COMPLIANCE.md      @dotlink-ops

# Environment configuration templates - contain secret keys structure
.env.example                @dotlink-ops
.env.local.example          @dotlink-ops

# Configuration files that may affect security
*.config.js                 @dotlink-ops
*.config.ts                 @dotlink-ops
*.config.mjs                @dotlink-ops

# Branch protection and code ownership itself
.github/CODEOWNERS          @dotlink-ops

# =============================================================================
# CRITICAL DOCUMENTATION
# =============================================================================

# Architecture and setup docs - define system behavior
ARCHITECTURE.md             @dotlink-ops
SETUP.md                    @dotlink-ops
TASK_HANDOFF.md             @dotlink-ops

# =============================================================================
# API & SENSITIVE DATA HANDLING
# =============================================================================

# API routes - may handle secrets or sensitive operations
app/api/                    @dotlink-ops

# =============================================================================
# DEFAULT FALLBACK
# =============================================================================

# Everything else in the repo (lower priority)
* @dotlink-ops

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
#
# Review Requirements:
# - All changes to critical paths above require approval from @dotlink-ops
# - Enforced by dot-rail branch ruleset for dot-rail and dot-rail/* branches
# - Protects automation infrastructure, security configs, and workflows
#
# To bypass (highly restricted):
# - Repository administrators only
# - Explicitly defined users in ruleset bypass list
#
# Priority Order:
# - Most specific paths are evaluated first (scripts/, .github/workflows/, python/)
# - Fallback to default owner (*) for unmatched paths
#
# Contact:
# - Access requests or questions: Open a GitHub issue
# - Urgent automation changes: Contact @dotlink-ops directly
